# Junior UI/UX Design Audit - 7-Agent Perspective

## 1. Brand Identity (Agent: Brand Strategist)
- **Issue**: Reliance on YouTube Red/White play button creates a "knock-off" feel.
- **Action**: Switch to a combination of Obsidian Black and VibeStream Gold (#FFB800). Use a more modern, slightly rounded triangle or a bespoke "V" play mark.

## 2. Accessibility & Ease of Use (Agent: UX Researcher)
- **Issue**: The central play button is not clickable. Users intuitively click the big icon.
- **Action**: Make the entire center overlay interactive. Ensure contrast ratios for text on videos are high.

## 3. Responsive Layout (Agent: Frontend Architect)
- **Issue**: Dashboard tables are cramped on mobile. Admin panels need better padding on tablets.
- **Action**: Implement horizontal scrolling for tables on mobile with sticky first columns. Adjust card grid spacing.

## 4. Visual Polish (Agent: Visual Designer)
- **Issue**: Typography weights are inconsistent. Some spacing feels ad-hoc.
- **Action**: Normalize font-weights (Inter/Outfit). Use a standard 4px/8px grid for all spacing.

## 5. Creator Experience (Agent: Creator Success)
- **Issue**: Video management is simple but feels "flat".
- **Action**: Add hover states that reveal metrics. Use micro-animations when saving metadata.

## 6. Admin Excellence (Agent: Platform Admin)
- **Issue**: Admin panel is functional but visually basic.
- **Action**: Use glassmorphsim and consistent card headers. Add "System Status" indicators.

## 7. Performance & Motion (Agent: Motion Designer)
- **Issue**: Transitions are standard.
- **Action**: Use Framer Motion for "staggered" entry of dashboard cards. Ensure play button expansion feels "weighted".
